law.text:
A contractor or subcontractor otherwise subject to the provisions of KRS 45.570 is exempt as to any affirmative action or reporting requirements if:
The contract or subcontract awarded is in the amount of five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) or less, and the amount of the contract is not a subterfuge to avoid compliance with the provisions of KRS 45.560 to 45.640;
The contractor or subcontractor utilizes the services of fewer than eight (8) employees during the course of the contract;
The contractor or subcontractor employs only family members or relatives;
The contractor or subcontractor employs only persons having a direct ownership interest in the business, and such interest is not a subterfuge to avoid compliance with the provisions of KRS 45.560 to 45.640; or
The subcontract is below the second-tier level of contracts.
